history.content: I would be extremely surprised if 170 isn't offered next semester. It has consistently been one of the largest upperdivs on campus and I'm confident that the EECS faculty will find a way to make it happen. That being said, most students who want to enroll in 170 usually get in, so finding a spot it isn't something that you need to worry about

Hello! I am worried about getting into EECS 126 since I am planning on taking 189 next summer. The class has filled up and there is now a waitlist of around ~70 people, and I kind of need the class. I was planning on taking 170 next semester, but considering it is currently unavailable, should I drop myself from 170s waitlist so I can join 126? Thanks.
history.subject: Should I stay enrolled in 170
